Your **CatalogueConfig** is abstracted from `django.apps.AppConfig`. You should abstract it from oscar&#39;s catalogue apps


    import oscar.apps.catalogue.apps as apps
    
    
    class CatalogueConfig(apps.CatalogueConfig):
        name = &#39;catalogue&#39;
        label= &#39;catalogue&#39; # this label must be this
        verbose_name = &#39;Catalogue&#39;

By the way. You don&#39;t need to manually do it, there is management command called [oscar_fork_app][1].


  [1]: https://django-oscar.readthedocs.io/en/2.0.0/topics/customisation.html#fork-oscar-app

